---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'How do I know if my roof needs restoration or full replacement?',
    answer: 'That\'s exactly what our free inspection determines. If your flat roof deck is structurally sound — no major rot, core failure, or standing water — restoration is almost always the better choice at 60–70% less cost. Our inspector gives you an honest assessment with photos, no sales pressure.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How long does a flat roof restoration take?',
    answer: 'Most flat roof restorations are completed in a single day. Larger commercial roofs (10,000+ sq ft) may take 2–3 days. Unlike full replacement, there\'s no tear-off or heavy debris — your tenants or business experience minimal disruption.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How much does restoration cost compared to replacement?',
    answer: 'Restoration typically costs $4–$8 per sq ft depending on condition and prep needed. A full replacement runs $15–$25+ per sq ft. On a 5,000 sq ft commercial roof, that\'s the difference between $20,000–$40,000 vs $75,000–$125,000.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you work on residential flat roofs?',
    answer: 'Yes. We restore and replace flat roofs on residential homes, townhomes, and condos across all of Florida. The process is the same — free inspection, itemized quote, and fast installation.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What roofing systems do you install for replacements?',
    answer: 'We install all major flat roof systems: TPO, EPDM, modified bitumen, built-up roofing (BUR), and silicone coating systems. We recommend the best fit for your building type, budget, and local climate after inspection.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Are you licensed and insured in Florida?',
    answer: 'Yes. We are fully licensed under Florida roofing contractor regulations and carry full general liability and workers\' compensation insurance. We can provide certificates of insurance before any work begins.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you pull permits for roofing work?',
    answer: 'Yes, for any work that requires a permit under Florida Building Code, we handle the permit process entirely — application, scheduling inspections, and final sign-off. You don\'t have to worry about compliance.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What warranty do you offer?',
    answer: 'Our restorations come with a 15-year manufacturer warranty on the coating system plus our workmanship guarantee. Replacements are covered by the manufacturer\'s material warranty plus our own workmanship warranty. All warranties are transferable to new owners.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do I prepare for a roof inspection?',
    answer: 'Nothing special is required. Just make sure we have access to the roof — either via interior hatch or exterior ladder. Our inspector will handle everything and provide you with a written report and photos within 24 hours.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you offer financing?',
    answer: 'Yes. We work with financing partners to offer flexible payment options — many clients can start with little or no money down. Ask about current programs when you schedule your free inspection.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do flat roofs handle Miami\'s hurricane season?',
    answer: 'Properly installed and maintained flat roofs perform well in hurricane conditions. We use Miami-Dade approved materials rated for high wind uplift. Silicone coating systems create a seamless membrane that eliminates seams — the most common point of failure during storms.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can a leaking flat roof be repaired without full restoration?',
    answer: 'Often yes — if the leak is isolated to a specific area (flashing, pipe penetration, seam), targeted repair can solve it quickly and affordably. We\'ll tell you honestly if a repair is the right fix or if the roof has broader issues that require a larger solution.',
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="py-24 lg:py-32 bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-slate-500 mb-4">
        <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-blue-500"></span>
        FAQ
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-slate-900 leading-tight mb-4">
        Common Questions Answered
      </h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-lg">
        Have more questions? Call us or request your free inspection — we'll address everything in person.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-2" id="faq-list">
      {faqs.map(({ question, answer }, index) => (
        <div
          class="faq-item border border-gray-100 bg-white hover:border-slate-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden transition-colors duration-200"
          data-index={index}
        >
          <button
            class="faq-trigger w-full flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 text-left group"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            <span class="text-slate-800 font-medium text-sm pr-4 group-hover:text-slate-900 transition-colors">
              {question}
            </span>
            <svg
              class="faq-icon w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform duration-300"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer hidden px-6 pb-5">
            <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-gray-100 pt-4">
              {answer}
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- Bottom CTA -->
    <div class="mt-12 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 bg-slate-50 text-center">
      <h3 class="text-slate-900 font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Still have questions?</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-6">Our team is happy to answer anything. No bots, no runaround — just real answers.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 justify-center">
        <a
          href="tel:+15550000000"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-6 py-2.5 border border-gray-200 bg-white text-slate-700 hover:border-slate-300 font-medium rounded-full text-sm transition-all"
        >
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 5a2 2 0 012-2h3.28a1 1 0 01.948.684l1.498 4.493a1 1 0 01-.502 1.21l-2.257 1.13a11.042 11.042 0 005.516 5.516l1.13-2.257a1 1 0 011.21-.502l4.493 1.498a1 1 0 01.684.949V19a2 2 0 01-2 2h-1C9.716 21 3 14.284 3 6V5z" />
          </svg>
          Call (555) 000-0000
        </a>
        <button
          data-modal="contact"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 pl-5 pr-1.5 py-1.5 bg-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-800 text-white text-sm font-semibold rounded-full transition-all"
        >
          Get Free Inspection
          <span class="w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-blue-500 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-white" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M7 17L17 7M17 7H7M17 7v10"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  const triggers = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-trigger');
  triggers.forEach((trigger) => {
    trigger.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const item = trigger.closest('.faq-item');
      const answer = item?.querySelector('.faq-answer');
      const icon = trigger.querySelector('.faq-icon');
      const isOpen = trigger.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';

      document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach((el) => {
        el.querySelector('.faq-answer')?.classList.add('hidden');
        el.querySelector('.faq-trigger')?.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
        el.querySelector('.faq-icon')?.classList.remove('rotate-180');
      });

      if (!isOpen) {
        answer?.classList.remove('hidden');
        trigger.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
        icon?.classList.add('rotate-180');
      }
    });
  });
</script>
